1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with capacity and performance metrics in wireless networks, which are key topics in information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on wireless network models and network coding strategies, which are relevant to the networking and internet architecture subfield. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a multi-objective optimization framework for wireless networks, which can be seen as a control problem. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper mentions delay and energy performance metrics, which are important in multimedia applications. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - Although the paper does not explicitly mention security, wireless networks are vulnerable to attacks and securing them is an important research area in cryptography and security.
